==English==

===Etymology===
[[Latin]]; ''vulva'' earlier ''volva'', "womb, female sexual organ", from ''volvare'', "to turn, wrap arround"

===Noun===
'''vulva''' (''plural'' '''vulvae''')

# {{anatomy}} external female sexual organs, collectively (including [[clitoris]]); "[[vagina]]" is often used to refer to the vulva or female genitals generally, even though strictly speaking the vagina is a specific internal structure. "Calling the vulva the vagina is akin to calling the mouth the throat."


